        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: #94432 classify Cloudflare challenge 403 as upstream_html instead of auth_html",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Detect Cloudflare browser-challenge HTML 403 responses from chatgpt.com/backend-api\n- Reclassify them as `upstream_html` instead of `auth_html`, surfacing a more accurate error message\n\n## Problem\n\nWhen the Codex provider makes server-side requests to `https://chatgpt.com/backend-api`, Cloudflare returns an HTML browser-challenge page with status 403. The error classification in `classifyProviderRuntimeFailureKind` treated ALL 403 HTML responses as `auth_html`, producing the misleading message:\n\n> \"Authentication failed at the provider. Re-authenticate and verify your provider credentials and account access.\"\n\nThis is incorrect — the Cloudflare challenge is a CDN/gateway block, not an authentication failure.\n\n## Fix\n\n- Added `CLOUDFLARE_CHALLENGE_RE` regex and `isCloudflareChallengeResponse()` helper to detect Cloudflare challenge pages (matching \"Enable JavaScript and cookies to continue\", \"cf-browser-verification\", \"__cf_challenge\")\n- In the `classifyProviderRuntimeFailureKind` function, Cloudflare challenge 403 is now classified as `upstream_html`, which surfaces the accurate message:\n\n> \"The provider returned an HTML error page instead of an API response. This usually means a CDN or gateway (e.g. Cloudflare) blocked the request.\"\n\n- Generic 403 HTML responses (non-Cloudflare) remain classified as `auth_html` — no regression.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm vitest run src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers/provider-error-patterns.test.ts` — 80 tests passed\n- New test: \"classifies Cloudflare challenge 403 as upstream_html\" — verifies the new behavior\n- Existing test: \"classifies generic 403 HTML runtime failures as auth_html\" — verifies no regression\n- Existing tests: \"classifies Cloudflare HTML 502 as timeout\", \"classifies 401 HTML as auth\" — unchanged behavior\n\n## Related Issue\n\nCloses #94432",
        "branch": "fix/issue-94432-cloudflare-challenge-error",
